    {"question": "Is Xero difficult to learn?", "answer": "Xero is significantly easier to use than traditional accounting software. Most founders can perform basic bookkeeping tasks (reconciling bank transactions, sending invoices, running reports) within a few hours of starting. Xero provides free learning resources at Xero Central. For complex accounting tasks (accruals, depreciation, intercompany transactions), working with an accountant familiar with Xero is recommended."},
    {"question": "How many bank accounts can I connect to Xero?", "answer": "Xero supports unlimited bank account connections. Connect your business current account, savings account, credit cards, and PayPal. Each connected account imports transactions automatically via the bank feed. For businesses operating accounts in multiple currencies, Xero''s multi-currency feature (available on Premium plan) handles foreign currency transactions with automatic exchange rate updates."},
    {"question": "Can my accountant access Xero?", "answer": "Yes — Xero is designed for collaborative accountant-client relationships. You invite your accountant as a user with their own login (advisor access allows them to post journals and access all features). Your accountant can work in your Xero file simultaneously without any data transfer or file sharing. This is the primary workflow for most startups using Xero — you handle day-to-day bookkeeping, your accountant handles period-end adjustments and tax filing."}
